# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# RBE Lab — Local Configuration
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to config.env and fill in your values.
# config.env is listed in .gitignore — it will NEVER be committed.
# It contains your GitHub PAT which must stay off Git.
#
#   cp cluster/config.env.example cluster/config.env
#   vim cluster/config.env
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Your GitHub repository URL (no trailing slash)
GITHUB_REPO=https://github.com/exitthematrix26/remote_builder

# GitHub Personal Access Token
# Required scopes:
#   - read:packages   → pull images from ghcr.io in the cluster
#   - write:packages  → (optional here, needed in GitHub Actions)
#
# Create at: https://github.com/settings/tokens → "Generate new token (classic)"
# Select scopes: read:packages (minimum for cluster pulls)
#
# In Phase 3 this PAT will be encrypted with kubeseal so the cluster pulls
# images automatically. For Phase 1/2, bootstrap.sh creates a plain K8s Secret
# from this value (only lives in cluster, never in Git).
GITHUB_PAT=ghp_REPLACE_WITH_YOUR_TOKEN

# Kind cluster name
# Must be unique on this machine. bootstrap.sh will refuse to create a cluster
# if this name already exists, protecting your other clusters (bazel-sim, bootik-local).
CLUSTER_NAME=remote-builder

# Argo CD initial admin password
# Leave blank to use the auto-generated password (recommended for first run).
# bootstrap.sh will print the auto-generated password at the end.
# If you want to set a specific password, set it here and bootstrap.sh will
# update it via argocd account update-password.
ARGOCD_ADMIN_PASSWORD=
